data.author: ge6P2xDQYLs9EAJh
data.text:
This scene was made to for small heists or local infiltrations. A high walled compound surrounds a two floor building with a small vault. On the ground floor there is an open lobby area which can be looked down upon from windows on the floor above. There is a small office off the lobby and an area for clerks to work undisturbed. A single file staircase allows access to the first floor and the vault itself. Towards the north-west corner of the first floor there is a managers office which overlooks the lobby and is situated close to the vault.

The garden inside the compound could be exactly what it appears to be, but some less reputable organisations might scatter some traps around there to discourage nighttime visitors. A crane outside the walls might represent a way in, but only for those possessing unusual acrobatics.

Around the outside of the compound there are five places where the walls can be broken and the gates can be knocked down. The building has an alarm system which sets off red lighting and can be used to raise the stakes. The vault door itself can also be blown open.
